[recto] Owner (with address) Dr. Joseph R. Feste, M.D., 7550 Fannin Street, Houston, Texas, 77054 bought at Sale [onleesbaar]. Measurements 17"x11,5" support (technique) Oil on canvas, N° 115 as Pieter Bruegel the Younger, July 10, 1971?[sic] Provenance: Sale by Auction (Auctioneer Jack H. Feldman, 861, N° La Cienega, Los Angeles. as P. Bruegel the Younger. Kept black & white Photograph for my documentation. Private address of Dr. Feste, 1341 Myrtlea, Houston, Texas ex. Hanema? [sic][Doorstreepte tekst]; [verso] Mrs. Jane Cox, William Pijper Straat 3, The Hague. Cousin of owner Dr. Feste came to me with all this documentation and very poor [doorstreept]: 'wrong' certificate full of mistakes by a Mr Lonson ...[sic] I refused to suggest any attribution or to examine the picture in the orginal. Why P.B.II ? Mrs Cox was sent to me by Dr. Ann [sic] Zwollo, Rijksbureau, The Hague, who was unable to suggest any attribution, except 'Student of Bruegel' & suggested to Mrs. Cox to look up files of Witt Library, Frick Reference Library. [Zeer zwak handschrift][scan]
